AstraZeneca, Sanofi Join Tuberculosis Initiative, Guardian Says

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-03-03T06:34:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/astrazeneca-sanofi-join-tuberculosis-initiative-guardian-says.html
  AstraZeneca Plc (AZN)  and  Sanofi-Aventis
SA (SAN)  have joined several European universities in a global
initiative to combat tuberculosis, the Guardian reported.  The group, which will get 16 million euros ($22 million) of
European Union funding, will be led by Stewart Cole, who heads
the global health institute at the Ecole Polytechnique Federale
de Lausanne, the newspaper said.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
